<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911210-0007</DOCNO><DOCID>911210-0007.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Standard Brands Paint Co.:   Founders Equity Sets Pact   For Infusion of $12 Million</HL><DATE>12/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C25</SO><CO>   SBP WNEWS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>SPECIALTY RETAILERS OF LIMITED PRODUCT LINES (OTS)ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)SECURITIES (SCR)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>FINANCING AGREEMENTS (FNC)PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)SHAREHOLDER RIGHTS PLANS (SRP)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Standard Brands Paint Co., Torrance, Calif., said itreached an agreement with Founders Equity Inc., a New Yorkinvestment group, for a capital infusion of about $12million.   Also, the company said Eric Beck will step down aspresident and chief operating officer of the paint retailerto pursue personal business interests. Carl A. Bellini, aformer Sherwin Williams Co. executive, has become actingchief operating officer, and is expected to be namedpresident at the next board meeting.</LP><TEXT>   The financing plan calls for the company to sell to agroup affiliated with Founders $6 million of its commonstock, and warrants to buy as much as 35% of the number ofshares initially purchased.   That sale would be conditioned on a rights offering toStandard Brands shareholders that would net the company anadditional $6 million. The company will offer shareholdersrights to buy its common stock for a maximum of $1.50 ashare, and the final price will be determined when the offerbecomes effective.</TEXT></DOC>